Trump=E2=80=99s Zero Hour, Globes Fashion Police,
Dolan=E2=80=99s MSG Nightmare
-------------------------------------------

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon guide to Puck=E2=80=99s
best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Matt Belloni offers up Part 1 of his 25 (probably) surefire=
 predictions (including several special guest submissions!) for the issues =
and events that will shape the entertainment industry over the coming year:=
 What happens to Michael Rubin=E2=80=99s infamous White Party? Will Amazon =
scoop up UFC? And could Rupert Murdoch
sell Fox News to=E2=80=A6 himself?

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Lauren Sherman chronicles the latest Kardashian heada=
ches as Kim=E2=80=99s private equity vehicle sputters and Kylie=E2=80=99s f=
ashion brand loses a partner. John Ourand digs into the R.S.N. showdown bet=
ween Jim Dolan=E2=80=99s MSG Networks and the troubled cable
distributor Altice. Peter Hamby assesses the time crunch facing Trump=E2=80=
=99s single-term presidency. And Matt scoops the price tag for Amazon=E2=80=
=99s Brett Ratner-directed Melania vanity documentary.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Meanwhile, in Puck=E2=80=99s podcast universe: Lucas Shaw joins The Town to=
 spar with Matt over this year=E2=80=99s Golden Globes. On Fashion
People, Lauren rings up entertainment journalist Zanna Roberts Rassi to pic=
